1
00:00:00,844 --> 00:00:02,319
In previous episodes,

2
00:00:02,344 --> 00:00:04,424
Tsubasa and his teammates
earned their right

3
00:00:04,554 --> 00:00:06,351
to participate in
the National Tournament.

4
00:00:06,376 --> 00:00:07,945
However,
Wakabayashi cannot play

5
00:00:08,468 --> 00:00:10,094
due to his injury.

6
00:00:10,819 --> 00:00:11,899
He was furious,

7
00:00:11,924 --> 00:00:13,674
but now,
he must continue to rest

8
00:00:13,699 --> 00:00:15,394
while his teammates
play without him.

9
00:00:15,729 --> 00:00:17,609
Tsubasa promised
Wakabayashi

10
00:00:17,634 --> 00:00:19,069
they would win
all the matches

11
00:00:19,094 --> 00:00:21,224
and he would be
ready to face Meiwa.

12
00:00:21,959 --> 00:00:24,007
The coach gave Tsubasa
the ribbon,

13
00:00:24,224 --> 00:00:27,648
making him the new
captain of the team!

14
00:00:28,411 --> 00:00:29,451
And then...

15
00:00:32,264 --> 00:00:33,304
Fellow players...

16
00:00:33,554 --> 00:00:34,594
Let's play in
this tournament

17
00:00:34,594 --> 00:00:37,054
showing honor and respect
to our opponents!

18
00:00:37,269 --> 00:00:38,319
Let's play with passion

19
00:00:38,344 --> 00:00:40,094
and a spirit of
good sportsmanship!

20
00:00:40,844 --> 00:00:42,384
I'm here representing
Nankatsu!

21
00:00:42,588 --> 00:00:43,588
My name is...

22
00:00:43,804 --> 00:00:45,304
Tsubasa Ozora!

23
00:00:46,648 --> 00:00:48,674
After a grand ovation,

24
00:00:48,699 --> 00:00:51,449
the National Tournament
finally began!

25
00:00:51,724 --> 00:00:53,779
And now,
the irony of fate

26
00:00:53,804 --> 00:00:55,031
gave the first kick,

27
00:00:55,056 --> 00:00:57,500
and Nankatsu
must now face Meiwa

28
00:00:57,525 --> 00:00:59,062
in their first match.

29
00:00:59,087 --> 00:01:00,717
Who will be victorious?

30
00:01:02,640 --> 00:01:05,470
All right! This match is
very important!

31
00:01:05,804 --> 00:01:07,239
I want you to give it
all you got!

32
00:01:07,264 --> 00:01:09,014
-Yes, Coach!
-Yes, Coach!

33
00:01:09,474 --> 00:01:10,304
Good shot!

34
00:01:10,424 --> 00:01:11,424
Next player!

35
00:01:11,564 --> 00:01:12,524
Here!

36
00:01:12,549 --> 00:01:14,234
I won't let you down!

37
00:01:14,344 --> 00:01:16,804
I'm sure that my foot
has healed by now.

38
00:01:17,424 --> 00:01:18,424
I'm begging you!

39
00:01:18,741 --> 00:01:20,111
Please wait until I heal!

40
00:01:20,674 --> 00:01:23,054
We'll have to face Meiwa
in the first match.

41
00:01:23,079 --> 00:01:25,174
But I don't care
what happens!

42
00:01:25,304 --> 00:01:26,634
We will win this match.

43
00:01:26,764 --> 00:01:28,224
I promise you we will win!

44
00:01:29,674 --> 00:01:31,724
That's how it's done,
Tsubasa!

45
00:01:31,724 --> 00:01:33,264
Yeah guys, that's right!

46
00:01:33,514 --> 00:01:35,554
Focus! Let's leave
everything on the pitch!

47
00:01:35,674 --> 00:01:37,424
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

48
00:01:37,770 --> 00:01:38,770
Team Meiwa...

49
00:01:38,974 --> 00:01:40,474
Are you ready to
come on out?

50
00:01:40,634 --> 00:01:42,304
Sorry for the--
Whoa!

51
00:01:45,094 --> 00:01:46,094
Hey there, Coach...

52
00:01:46,264 --> 00:01:47,474
it's time to go now.

53
00:01:47,634 --> 00:01:48,804
Okay, go ahead, then!

54
00:01:48,924 --> 00:01:49,924
I'll catch up to you.

55
00:01:49,949 --> 00:01:52,594
It doesn't matter if I'm there
with you guys now.

56
00:01:54,027 --> 00:01:56,467
MEIWA FC COACH
KOZO KIRA

57
00:01:56,764 --> 00:01:58,634
He always prefers
to stay and drink.

58
00:01:58,902 --> 00:02:01,062
A coach should not
behave like that.

59
00:02:01,174 --> 00:02:02,174
Yes...

60
00:02:02,199 --> 00:02:03,409
But even so, Coach Kira

61
00:02:03,434 --> 00:02:05,344
trained Hyuga and Sawada
from the start.

62
00:02:05,376 --> 00:02:07,203
That's made us
a very strong team.

63
00:02:07,228 --> 00:02:08,724
He's a very good coach.

64
00:02:09,474 --> 00:02:12,594
Kojiro, your only objective
is to win.

65
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:15,670
The end justifies the means.
Don't forget that.

66
00:02:16,371 --> 00:02:17,371
All right.

67
00:02:18,674 --> 00:02:21,224
Wow! There's
a lot of traffic today.

68
00:02:21,674 --> 00:02:23,594
I've driven through here
many times, but I...

69
00:02:23,594 --> 00:02:25,304
I've never seen it
like this.

70
00:02:25,804 --> 00:02:27,069
That means that
today's game

71
00:02:27,094 --> 00:02:28,474
has drawn lots of attention.

72
00:02:28,764 --> 00:02:30,054
I bet that it will be...

73
00:02:30,424 --> 00:02:31,634
very interesting.

74
00:02:31,924 --> 00:02:34,514
I wonder who will be
the most outstanding player.

75
00:02:34,765 --> 00:02:36,185
We will see that very soon.

76
00:02:36,474 --> 00:02:37,474
We sure will.

77
00:02:38,234 --> 00:02:43,244
[opening theme]

78
00:04:21,948 --> 00:04:25,104
Episode 14:
Nankatsu versus Meiwa.

79
00:04:25,129 --> 00:04:26,799
The matches
of the National Tournament

80
00:04:26,972 --> 00:04:29,852
will take place on different
pitches simultaneously.

81
00:04:29,877 --> 00:04:31,377
Before we start
the first match,

82
00:04:31,578 --> 00:04:33,198
something that
we've never seen before

83
00:04:33,223 --> 00:04:34,299
is taking place!

84
00:04:36,604 --> 00:04:38,666
The stadium
is almost completely

85
00:04:38,691 --> 00:04:40,988
full of spectators
that came to see the match

86
00:04:40,988 --> 00:04:43,868
between Team Nankatsu
and Team Meiwa.

87
00:04:44,572 --> 00:04:46,782
There are so many
people here, Roberto!

88
00:04:46,893 --> 00:04:48,053
That's right.

89
00:04:48,078 --> 00:04:49,618
There weren't this much
people in Brazil...

90
00:04:49,643 --> 00:04:51,943
which is the country where
everyone loves football.

91
00:04:52,103 --> 00:04:53,893
Hey, good thing
we arrived on time.

92
00:04:53,963 --> 00:04:55,618
Yeah, and now we will see

93
00:04:55,643 --> 00:04:57,353
who is the best of
these two teams.

94
00:04:57,695 --> 00:05:00,235
Holy cow! There are
so many people here!

95
00:05:00,444 --> 00:05:02,604
Hey, Taro,
don't let us down today!

96
00:05:02,629 --> 00:05:03,209
Huh?

97
00:05:03,234 --> 00:05:05,564
We will be here
supporting you, all right?

98
00:05:05,589 --> 00:05:06,929
Thanks a lot, Hikaru!

99
00:05:07,105 --> 00:05:09,025
I'll make sure I won't
let you down!

100
00:05:09,328 --> 00:05:11,738
You can do it, Tsubasa,
you're the best!

101
00:05:11,789 --> 00:05:13,039
This will be interesting.

102
00:05:13,284 --> 00:05:14,284
Huh?

103
00:05:14,510 --> 00:05:16,198
I wonder which of
these teams

104
00:05:16,223 --> 00:05:17,513
will be the best rival.

105
00:05:19,683 --> 00:05:21,093
Look, the players for Meiwa

106
00:05:21,118 --> 00:05:23,028
-are coming now!
-Ohhh!

107
00:05:24,047 --> 00:05:25,957
It's been a while, Nankatsu.

108
00:05:26,656 --> 00:05:29,046
Kojiro Hyuga, that idiot.

109
00:05:32,259 --> 00:05:34,799
You're the little twerp
who spoke moments ago, huh?

110
00:05:36,198 --> 00:05:37,238
I'm going to show you

111
00:05:37,263 --> 00:05:38,933
the true spirit
of the sport!

112
00:05:40,578 --> 00:05:43,658
We are the team that will
win the National Torunament!

113
00:05:43,683 --> 00:05:44,683
Since you are the team
we face

114
00:05:44,708 --> 00:05:45,588
in the opening match...

115
00:05:45,613 --> 00:05:47,323
you'll be the first to lose!

116
00:05:49,799 --> 00:05:51,629
You stupid idiot!

117
00:05:57,807 --> 00:06:00,517
Both teams
are now in their positions.

118
00:06:00,542 --> 00:06:01,922
Team Nankatsu,
well known for

119
00:06:02,448 --> 00:06:02,678
their excellent passing,

120
00:06:02,678 --> 00:06:03,988
their excellent passing,
NANKATSU SC

121
00:06:03,988 --> 00:06:04,118
NANKATSU SC

122
00:06:04,118 --> 00:06:06,188
NANKATSU SC
are representing the Shizuoka Prefecture.

123
00:06:06,188 --> 00:06:06,618
are representing the Shizuoka Prefecture.

124
00:06:06,768 --> 00:06:07,128
NANKATSU SC

125
00:06:07,128 --> 00:06:08,858
NANKATSU SC
They use a 4-3-3 formation.

126
00:06:08,858 --> 00:06:08,971
They use a 4-3-3 formation.

127
00:06:09,658 --> 00:06:10,988
We know
their star goalkeeper

128
00:06:11,013 --> 00:06:12,118
Genzo Wakabayashi...

129
00:06:12,238 --> 00:06:14,868
will not play in today's
match due to an injury.

130
00:06:14,893 --> 00:06:17,440
In his place,
Yuzo Morisaki.

131
00:06:18,369 --> 00:06:20,699
Shingo Takasugi is
the leader of the defense.

132
00:06:20,724 --> 00:06:23,564
It'll be very difficult
to get past them!

133
00:06:24,218 --> 00:06:26,995
At the midfield positions,
we have Taro Misaki,

134
00:06:27,020 --> 00:06:29,096
Mamoru Izawa,
and Hanji Urabe.

135
00:06:29,121 --> 00:06:31,831
And at forward, we have
Hajime Taki, Teppei Kisugi,

136
00:06:31,856 --> 00:06:34,226
and Tsubasa Ozora
as the Center Forward.

137
00:06:34,733 --> 00:06:35,393
All right, guys!

138
00:06:35,418 --> 00:06:36,748
I want you to leave it
all on the field!

139
00:06:36,999 --> 00:06:38,199
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

140
00:06:39,398 --> 00:06:39,808
Their opponent today is Team Meiwa,

141
00:06:39,808 --> 00:06:41,508
Their opponent today is Team Meiwa,
MEIWA FC

142
00:06:41,528 --> 00:06:42,768
with a 4-4-2 formation.

143
00:06:43,222 --> 00:06:45,222
Kojiro Hyuga,
a.k.a. The Tiger,

144
00:06:45,572 --> 00:06:46,402
is their Center Forward

145
00:06:46,427 --> 00:06:48,007
who's going to try to
score goals!

146
00:06:48,398 --> 00:06:50,518
At his side will be
Takeshi Sawada,

147
00:06:50,543 --> 00:06:52,721
the captain for
today's match.

148
00:06:53,078 --> 00:06:54,828
Let's see how
this dynamic duo

149
00:06:54,853 --> 00:06:56,483
will play together
on the pitch!

150
00:06:56,948 --> 00:06:59,158
And in charge of
the line of defense today

151
00:06:59,183 --> 00:07:01,983
is goalkeeper
Yuji Kawaguchi!

152
00:07:04,384 --> 00:07:05,674
How crazy is this?!

153
00:07:05,699 --> 00:07:07,079
There are so many people!

154
00:07:07,104 --> 00:07:08,314
It'll be a great show!

155
00:07:10,733 --> 00:07:12,683
Kojiro, now is the time.

156
00:07:12,708 --> 00:07:14,612
Take control
during this match,

157
00:07:14,637 --> 00:07:16,727
and impress them
with your power!

158
00:07:18,417 --> 00:07:19,917
The match
between Nankatsu and Meiwa

159
00:07:19,942 --> 00:07:20,852
is about to begin!

160
00:07:20,877 --> 00:07:23,082
Meiwa will start
with the kick-off!

161
00:07:23,172 --> 00:07:24,882
The referee takes
a look at his stopwatch!

162
00:07:26,158 --> 00:07:28,238
There is no way
I'm losing this match!

163
00:07:28,507 --> 00:07:29,717
Come here!

164
00:07:30,206 --> 00:07:32,778
The captain
of Nankatsu, Tsubasa Ozora,

165
00:07:32,908 --> 00:07:34,495
shows his superior
ball-dribbling skills.

166
00:07:34,573 --> 00:07:36,698
But star player
Kojiro Hyuga

167
00:07:36,828 --> 00:07:38,198
closes in to steal
the ball from him!

168
00:07:38,223 --> 00:07:39,913
Meiwa's players look
very confident.

169
00:07:44,917 --> 00:07:46,408
Tsubasa and Hyuga

170
00:07:46,433 --> 00:07:48,023
kick the ball
at the same time!

171
00:07:49,578 --> 00:07:51,658
And the ball
goes flying into the air!

172
00:07:51,873 --> 00:07:54,423
The force of both players
sent the ball skyrocketing!

173
00:07:54,448 --> 00:07:55,598
You little twerp!

174
00:07:58,354 --> 00:07:59,988
-Taki!
-I got it.

175
00:08:00,385 --> 00:08:01,635
You'll see, idiot!

176
00:08:03,828 --> 00:08:05,828
What's this?!
My leg!

177
00:08:05,853 --> 00:08:08,853
My leg's numb from
the impact with Kojiro!

178
00:08:13,652 --> 00:08:15,992
Kojiro Hyuga can't move
to go get the ball!

179
00:08:16,238 --> 00:08:18,303
Nankatsu now has
a golden opportunity

180
00:08:18,423 --> 00:08:19,503
to score a goal!

181
00:08:19,528 --> 00:08:20,408
Teppei!

182
00:08:20,528 --> 00:08:22,238
Yes!
Now leave it all up to me!

183
00:08:23,057 --> 00:08:26,368
The ball is recovered by
Takeshi Sawada of Meiwa,

184
00:08:26,393 --> 00:08:27,963
who is
a fourth-grade student,

185
00:08:27,988 --> 00:08:30,698
and we will certainly
be watching him closely!

186
00:08:31,078 --> 00:08:31,908
No!

187
00:08:32,028 --> 00:08:33,028
Takeshi!

188
00:08:34,578 --> 00:08:35,988
Give me the ball!

189
00:08:36,369 --> 00:08:37,369
What?!

190
00:08:40,401 --> 00:08:42,174
-No way!
-What a beautiful play!

191
00:08:42,199 --> 00:08:45,118
I can't believe Sawada
is only a fourth-grade boy!

192
00:08:45,143 --> 00:08:46,368
Thanks to his skill,

193
00:08:46,488 --> 00:08:48,738
Meiwa have the chance
to score the first goal!

194
00:08:48,763 --> 00:08:50,843
It seems my leg
is no longer numb!

195
00:08:51,198 --> 00:08:52,988
I'm with you, Takeshi!

196
00:08:53,013 --> 00:08:55,383
This is
the true style of play

197
00:08:55,408 --> 00:08:57,198
of the Meiwa forwards!

198
00:08:57,459 --> 00:08:58,489
-Hey, Takeshi...
-Huh?

199
00:08:58,838 --> 00:09:00,338
You've improved quite a lot!

200
00:09:00,760 --> 00:09:03,143
Hi, Taro, great to see you!

201
00:09:03,471 --> 00:09:04,252
Thank you!

202
00:09:04,277 --> 00:09:05,738
Mr. Kira was my coach,

203
00:09:05,763 --> 00:09:07,343
and that's why I play
like this!

204
00:09:08,290 --> 00:09:10,890
He's the same person
who trained Hyuga!

205
00:09:10,915 --> 00:09:12,625
Now, I'll show you
how much I've improved!

206
00:09:13,350 --> 00:09:14,549
Takeshi Sawada
puts the ball

207
00:09:14,574 --> 00:09:16,495
-through Taro's legs!
-How's that?

208
00:09:17,698 --> 00:09:18,278
Huh?

209
00:09:18,303 --> 00:09:20,593
But Misaki
has cat-like reflexes!

210
00:09:20,618 --> 00:09:21,988
-Nice play!
-That's it, Taro!

211
00:09:22,013 --> 00:09:22,883
Takeshi Sawada

212
00:09:22,908 --> 00:09:24,318
couldn't get past
Taro Misaki!

213
00:09:24,482 --> 00:09:25,942
Taro, you surprised me.

214
00:09:26,228 --> 00:09:28,803
Misaki, if I would've
had the ball,

215
00:09:28,828 --> 00:09:30,908
I would've scored
the first goal!

216
00:09:35,408 --> 00:09:36,448
Huh? Whoa!

217
00:09:40,620 --> 00:09:41,926
Excuse me, sir,

218
00:09:41,951 --> 00:09:44,003
could you tell us
how Nankatsu's doing

219
00:09:44,028 --> 00:09:45,028
in their match?

220
00:09:45,053 --> 00:09:46,878
Taro Misaki
runs down field

221
00:09:46,903 --> 00:09:47,943
at high speed!

222
00:09:47,968 --> 00:09:49,798
There's no doubt that
he's a true prodigy!

223
00:09:49,823 --> 00:09:51,693
You won't get past us,
Misaki!

224
00:09:54,738 --> 00:09:55,738
Huh, what?

225
00:09:55,763 --> 00:09:58,053
Taro Misaki stops
and sends a long pass!

226
00:09:58,278 --> 00:10:01,278
The ball flies directly
toward Captain Tsubasa!

227
00:10:01,583 --> 00:10:03,033
What an excellent pass!

228
00:10:03,058 --> 00:10:04,368
Nankatsu has a chance

229
00:10:04,393 --> 00:10:06,393
to score the first goal
of the match!

230
00:10:06,815 --> 00:10:07,815
Okay.

231
00:10:10,698 --> 00:10:11,948
What's going on?!

232
00:10:11,948 --> 00:10:14,028
Tsubasa changes direction
toward Hyuga,

233
00:10:14,053 --> 00:10:15,973
and it looks like
he wants to challenge him!

234
00:10:15,998 --> 00:10:17,633
He will lose
his chance to shoot

235
00:10:17,658 --> 00:10:18,908
going directly
toward him!

236
00:10:18,933 --> 00:10:21,603
You think you can mock me,
you weakling?

237
00:10:21,628 --> 00:10:22,878
Don't make me laugh!

238
00:10:22,907 --> 00:10:25,527
I'll show you
who I really am, idiot!

239
00:10:27,351 --> 00:10:28,181
What?

240
00:10:28,206 --> 00:10:30,706
The... The ball...
It disappeared!

241
00:10:31,284 --> 00:10:33,114
But...what's this?!

242
00:10:33,608 --> 00:10:34,868
Ah! He did a--

243
00:10:35,528 --> 00:10:36,528
Hmm...

244
00:10:37,723 --> 00:10:39,883
Oh...
This is incredible!

245
00:10:39,908 --> 00:10:41,133
Tsubasa mocks Hyuga

246
00:10:41,158 --> 00:10:42,488
flipping the ball
in the air,

247
00:10:42,513 --> 00:10:44,213
and it passes over him!

248
00:10:44,238 --> 00:10:46,028
It floats over him
smoothly!

249
00:10:46,028 --> 00:10:47,738
Tsubasa gets in and...

250
00:10:48,988 --> 00:10:51,028
He puts
a shot on goal!

251
00:11:01,278 --> 00:11:03,988
Yay, Tsubasa, you did it!

252
00:11:05,078 --> 00:11:06,578
Goal!

253
00:11:06,698 --> 00:11:08,448
Tsubasa scores
in three minutes

254
00:11:08,578 --> 00:11:10,868
into the first half
of the match!

255
00:11:10,988 --> 00:11:12,828
Meiwa will not win
this match!

256
00:11:12,853 --> 00:11:14,023
It'll be Nankatsu!

257
00:11:15,415 --> 00:11:17,325
What an impressive shot!

258
00:11:17,517 --> 00:11:18,637
That was
the center forward

259
00:11:18,662 --> 00:11:20,082
for Team Nankatsu.

260
00:11:20,448 --> 00:11:22,972
He is practically
an unknown talent

261
00:11:23,214 --> 00:11:24,053
on the national level,

262
00:11:24,078 --> 00:11:25,448
who just scored
his first goal

263
00:11:25,473 --> 00:11:27,973
against the mighty
Team Meiwa.

264
00:11:28,198 --> 00:11:29,078
Huh?!

265
00:11:29,103 --> 00:11:31,167
What do you mean
unknown talent, stupid?!

266
00:11:31,299 --> 00:11:33,219
By now, you should've been
dreaming about him,

267
00:11:33,244 --> 00:11:35,034
you ignorant commentator!

268
00:11:35,408 --> 00:11:36,753
-That boy plays at
-Yeahs, that's how

269
00:11:36,778 --> 00:11:38,028
-a high level for his age.
-it's done!

270
00:11:38,028 --> 00:11:40,828
It's hard to believe he's
an elementary school boy!

271
00:11:40,853 --> 00:11:41,943
On my count!

272
00:11:42,097 --> 00:11:43,017
-We will, we will,
-We will, we will,

273
00:11:43,042 --> 00:11:43,729
-we will win!
-we will win!

274
00:11:43,754 --> 00:11:44,924
-We will, we will,
-We will, we will,

275
00:11:44,949 --> 00:11:45,956
-we will win!
-we will win!

276
00:11:46,458 --> 00:11:47,658
Very nice!

277
00:11:47,778 --> 00:11:48,868
For this match,

278
00:11:48,893 --> 00:11:51,273
I'm going to support
Team Nankatsu!

279
00:11:51,728 --> 00:11:54,188
Defeated by
Tsubasa's incredible skill,

280
00:11:54,213 --> 00:11:57,003
Hyuga looks completely
rattled right now.

281
00:11:57,028 --> 00:11:59,213
We'll have to see if he
can regain his composure,

282
00:11:59,238 --> 00:12:01,698
and launch
a counterattack to equalize!

283
00:12:01,723 --> 00:12:02,433
Hyuga...

284
00:12:02,948 --> 00:12:05,028
When you came to spy on us
during training,

285
00:12:05,053 --> 00:12:06,883
you refused to watch
any longer.

286
00:12:07,238 --> 00:12:09,408
If you had stayed,
you would've noticed

287
00:12:09,578 --> 00:12:12,118
the innate talent
that Tsubasa possesses.

288
00:12:12,618 --> 00:12:14,050
Forgive me, Kojiro.

289
00:12:14,553 --> 00:12:15,553
It's my fault,

290
00:12:15,578 --> 00:12:17,828
I let Misaki
take the ball from me.

291
00:12:19,828 --> 00:12:21,238
Ko... Kojiro!

292
00:12:28,401 --> 00:12:30,550
Yes, I know that look.

293
00:12:31,196 --> 00:12:33,856
I can see it in your eyes,
my boy.

294
00:12:34,689 --> 00:12:36,769
The eye of the tiger.

295
00:12:37,158 --> 00:12:40,118
We'll be right back,
with Captain Tsubasa.

296
00:12:45,804 --> 00:12:47,764
AFFILIATION: MEIWA FC BIRTHDAY: AUGUST 17 HEIGHT: 158 CM WEIGHT: 50 KG BLOOD TYPE: O

297
00:12:52,994 --> 00:12:55,824
Meiwa will kick off again
to start the second half.

298
00:12:57,784 --> 00:13:00,574
But Nankatsu
quickly takes the ball away!

299
00:13:00,599 --> 00:13:01,821
After the goal,

300
00:13:02,899 --> 00:13:05,994
the crowd fully supports
Nankatsu!

301
00:13:06,124 --> 00:13:07,244
Now, it's my turn!

302
00:13:07,269 --> 00:13:08,639
I'll score the second goal!

303
00:13:09,114 --> 00:13:10,114
No!

304
00:13:10,674 --> 00:13:11,674
Captain Hyuga!

305
00:13:11,874 --> 00:13:13,824
What's wrong
with Kojiro Hyuga?

306
00:13:13,824 --> 00:13:16,324
He's leaning on
one of the goalposts!

307
00:13:20,695 --> 00:13:21,815
Teppei Kisugi shoots!

308
00:13:22,686 --> 00:13:23,886
The goalie
can't stop it!

309
00:13:23,911 --> 00:13:24,874
Will it go in?!

310
00:13:25,089 --> 00:13:26,719
Off the post,
off the post!

311
00:13:26,744 --> 00:13:27,324
No!

312
00:13:27,349 --> 00:13:29,599
And Kojiro Hyuga
didn't even flinch!

313
00:13:30,524 --> 00:13:32,504
Takeshi Sawada kicks
the ball off the bounce

314
00:13:32,529 --> 00:13:33,669
and sends it
out of the box.

315
00:13:34,044 --> 00:13:34,824
It's mine!

316
00:13:34,907 --> 00:13:36,697
But Tsubasa
intercepts the ball

317
00:13:36,722 --> 00:13:38,352
-and attacks again!
-Yeah, Tsubasa!

318
00:13:38,377 --> 00:13:39,337
-Go, go!
-Go, go!

319
00:13:39,362 --> 00:13:40,704
-Come on Tsubasa,
-Come on, Tsubasa!

320
00:13:40,729 --> 00:13:43,109
-keep going!
-You got this!

321
00:13:43,324 --> 00:13:44,744
Meiwa can't stop him,

322
00:13:45,099 --> 00:13:46,969
and it seems Hyuga
is a statue!

323
00:13:46,994 --> 00:13:48,244
Why is he doing that?

324
00:13:48,374 --> 00:13:49,784
Kojiro, wake up!

325
00:13:49,784 --> 00:13:51,324
Tsubasa's approaching!

326
00:13:52,824 --> 00:13:55,164
I won't let you
make a mockery of me!

327
00:13:55,574 --> 00:13:57,824
Woah, Kojiro Hyuga
awakes from a trance

328
00:13:57,849 --> 00:13:59,824
and heads directly
toward Tsubasa Ozora.

329
00:13:59,954 --> 00:14:01,324
It seems he was
waiting for Tsubasa

330
00:14:01,349 --> 00:14:02,639
to attack the net!

331
00:14:02,874 --> 00:14:04,824
This... This will be
the second duel

332
00:14:04,824 --> 00:14:06,074
between these
two players.

333
00:14:06,204 --> 00:14:07,994
Hyuga heads directly
toward Tsubasa

334
00:14:08,019 --> 00:14:09,639
to take away the ball!

335
00:14:09,874 --> 00:14:11,016
You're not going
any further!

336
00:14:12,164 --> 00:14:13,874
Take this!

337
00:14:14,994 --> 00:14:16,759
Hyuga makes
a sliding tackle,

338
00:14:16,784 --> 00:14:18,324
and Tsubasa tries to
avoid it!

339
00:14:18,574 --> 00:14:20,204
Yeah, come on, Kojiro!

340
00:14:20,644 --> 00:14:21,324
Wow!

341
00:14:21,349 --> 00:14:24,269
He's trapped by Hyuga,
who stops him with his foot!

342
00:14:26,374 --> 00:14:28,324
-Tsu... Tsubasa!
-Tsu... Tsubasa!

343
00:14:29,391 --> 00:14:31,164
Tsubasa
falls to the ground,

344
00:14:31,379 --> 00:14:32,969
but the ref doesn't
call a foul

345
00:14:32,994 --> 00:14:35,034
and allows play
to continue!

346
00:14:35,244 --> 00:14:37,124
What a brutal fall!

347
00:14:37,454 --> 00:14:38,719
Hyuga's determination

348
00:14:38,744 --> 00:14:40,744
seems to be taking over
the match!

349
00:14:40,874 --> 00:14:43,454
Your team will not
win this tournament!

350
00:14:43,574 --> 00:14:44,824
-Idiot!
-You'll see!

351
00:14:44,824 --> 00:14:46,798
You'll pay for what
you did to Tsubasa!

352
00:14:46,823 --> 00:14:48,733
Move to the side, idiots!

353
00:14:48,930 --> 00:14:50,680
Kojiro Hyuga
gets ready to shoot!

354
00:14:51,124 --> 00:14:52,719
What?!
From that distance?

355
00:14:52,744 --> 00:14:54,324
Defend the goal!
Move it, guys!

356
00:14:55,324 --> 00:14:57,824
Now you'll see
how terrible we are!

357
00:14:59,244 --> 00:15:02,074
We are Team Meiwa!

358
00:15:04,914 --> 00:15:06,664
What'd he do?
Where's the ball?

359
00:15:06,689 --> 00:15:07,779
-It disappeared!
-It disappeared!

360
00:15:14,124 --> 00:15:16,244
G... G... Goal!

361
00:15:16,374 --> 00:15:17,874
The force knocks down
the goalie

362
00:15:17,994 --> 00:15:19,414
and the ball's
in the net!

363
00:15:22,724 --> 00:15:24,744
-Whoa!
-Whoa!

364
00:15:24,874 --> 00:15:27,244
You did it, Kojiro!!

365
00:15:27,269 --> 00:15:28,559
Incredible!

366
00:15:28,584 --> 00:15:29,834
He's so powerful!

367
00:15:30,164 --> 00:15:32,179
Yes,
this is the true strength

368
00:15:32,204 --> 00:15:34,624
of star player
Kojiro Hyuga!

369
00:15:34,744 --> 00:15:36,784
Meiwa just scored
the equalizer.

370
00:15:36,884 --> 00:15:39,714
We now have a tied match
on our hands!

371
00:15:40,394 --> 00:15:41,394
No way!

372
00:15:41,419 --> 00:15:43,374
He shot directly
at the goalie's face.

373
00:15:43,784 --> 00:15:45,124
But why did he do that?

374
00:15:45,374 --> 00:15:46,664
Very good!

375
00:15:46,689 --> 00:15:48,609
That's how it's done,
my boy!

376
00:15:48,974 --> 00:15:50,284
Yuzo, are you okay?

377
00:15:51,609 --> 00:15:52,899
I'm...afraid!

378
00:15:54,779 --> 00:15:56,609
You are an imbecile, Hyuga!

379
00:15:57,264 --> 00:15:58,494
Nankatsu and Meiwa

380
00:15:58,624 --> 00:16:00,704
are now tied
at one goal apiece!

381
00:16:00,824 --> 00:16:02,704
It's a battle between
Tsubasa and Hyuga.

382
00:16:02,824 --> 00:16:03,824
What?

383
00:16:06,251 --> 00:16:07,251
Humph!

384
00:16:09,744 --> 00:16:11,454
Aggression and passion.

385
00:16:11,914 --> 00:16:13,494
-Huh?
-Nothing.

386
00:16:13,624 --> 00:16:15,664
Tsubasa's style of play
is based on passion,

387
00:16:15,784 --> 00:16:17,454
and Hyuga's style
is based on aggression.

388
00:16:17,574 --> 00:16:19,494
-They're opposites.
-Ah, I see now.

389
00:16:19,824 --> 00:16:21,874
But it's not just this.

390
00:16:22,454 --> 00:16:24,854
Tsubasa enjoys
each movement on the field,

391
00:16:24,879 --> 00:16:26,509
with a big smile
on his face.

392
00:16:26,534 --> 00:16:28,954
And he moves as if the ball
were a part of him.

393
00:16:29,693 --> 00:16:30,563
On the other hand,

394
00:16:30,588 --> 00:16:32,874
Hyuga plays with
great determination...

395
00:16:33,099 --> 00:16:34,849
and channels his spirit
in each shot

396
00:16:34,874 --> 00:16:36,574
and turns into
a dominant player.

397
00:16:36,765 --> 00:16:37,805
Exactly.

398
00:16:38,462 --> 00:16:40,599
And plus, the coaches
from both teams

399
00:16:40,624 --> 00:16:42,034
are also very different.

400
00:16:42,164 --> 00:16:43,324
Yes, I know.

401
00:16:43,507 --> 00:16:45,977
Tsubasa received training
from Roberto Hongo.

402
00:16:46,374 --> 00:16:47,664
And Kozo Kira,
on the other hand,

403
00:16:47,689 --> 00:16:48,729
is the one
who trained Hyuga.

404
00:16:49,672 --> 00:16:51,789
Although there was
no professional league...

405
00:16:52,284 --> 00:16:53,599
a foreign football scout

406
00:16:53,624 --> 00:16:55,624
offered Kira
a spot on his team,

407
00:16:55,784 --> 00:16:56,929
but he rejected it,

408
00:16:56,954 --> 00:16:59,414
and nothing was known
about him for some time.

409
00:16:59,784 --> 00:17:01,744
Both disappeared,
then came back as coaches.

410
00:17:02,164 --> 00:17:02,954
Yes.

411
00:17:03,074 --> 00:17:06,034
Anyway, we really only need
to pick one player.

412
00:17:06,969 --> 00:17:08,299
The result of this match
will tell us

413
00:17:08,324 --> 00:17:11,704
which of these two
is the outstanding player.

414
00:17:13,494 --> 00:17:14,875
The score is still tied,

415
00:17:14,914 --> 00:17:16,784
and Nankatsu is on
the attack again.

416
00:17:16,914 --> 00:17:18,074
You got this, Misaki!

417
00:17:18,204 --> 00:17:19,454
-You got it!
-You got it!

418
00:17:19,574 --> 00:17:20,414
All right!

419
00:17:20,439 --> 00:17:23,109
Ah! Takeshi Sawada
tries to steal the ball!

420
00:17:23,328 --> 00:17:26,034
But Taro Misaki
won't let him get close!

421
00:17:26,164 --> 00:17:28,394
Looks like Misaki
still has the advantage!

422
00:17:28,594 --> 00:17:29,594
Taro!

423
00:17:30,164 --> 00:17:31,034
Incredible!

424
00:17:31,164 --> 00:17:32,244
Taro Misaki passes
to Teppei Kisugi!

425
00:17:32,374 --> 00:17:33,244
Tsubasa!

426
00:17:33,374 --> 00:17:35,664
And Teppei launches
a long pass.

427
00:17:36,445 --> 00:17:38,074
That's it, Teppei, good job!

428
00:17:38,204 --> 00:17:40,374
The ball is once again
controlled by Tsubasa.

429
00:17:41,274 --> 00:17:42,034
Listen up!

430
00:17:42,164 --> 00:17:43,954
I want everyone
to cover Tsubasa!

431
00:17:44,074 --> 00:17:45,639
Don't even let him
take a breath!

432
00:17:45,664 --> 00:17:46,244
Do you hear me?!

433
00:17:46,374 --> 00:17:47,954
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

434
00:17:48,074 --> 00:17:49,124
Uh, uh!

435
00:17:49,664 --> 00:17:50,844
Kojiro Hyuga
gives an order

436
00:17:50,869 --> 00:17:51,914
to mark Tsubasa,

437
00:17:52,034 --> 00:17:54,016
and the team runs quickly
toward him!

438
00:17:54,494 --> 00:17:56,414
-Take this!
-Take this!

439
00:17:57,486 --> 00:17:59,916
It's a barrage of
sliding tackles, folks!

440
00:18:00,058 --> 00:18:01,128
Tsubasa's trapped,

441
00:18:01,153 --> 00:18:02,483
but he is trying to
avoid them!

442
00:18:04,655 --> 00:18:06,063
Ah, stop that!

443
00:18:06,124 --> 00:18:07,624
That's a dangerous play!

444
00:18:07,839 --> 00:18:08,969
They're not just
going for the ball,

445
00:18:08,994 --> 00:18:10,284
they want to hit him, too!

446
00:18:11,055 --> 00:18:12,784
They're
going after Tsubasa!

447
00:18:13,531 --> 00:18:15,648
But he's able to
avoid them!

448
00:18:17,374 --> 00:18:20,204
Ah, the defender kicks
Tsubasa in the knee

449
00:18:20,229 --> 00:18:21,729
and he falls quickly
to the ground!

450
00:18:21,754 --> 00:18:23,244
-No! Tsubasa!
-No! Tsubasa!

451
00:18:24,429 --> 00:18:25,389
Tsubasa's
on the ground,

452
00:18:25,414 --> 00:18:28,139
and apparently this will
warrant a yellow card.

453
00:18:28,164 --> 00:18:29,398
And now we see it!

454
00:18:29,423 --> 00:18:30,883
-Do you see now?
-Oh!

455
00:18:31,414 --> 00:18:33,391
We'll commit
all the fouls we can!

456
00:18:33,462 --> 00:18:35,539
Don't even let this twerp
move an inch!

457
00:18:35,788 --> 00:18:36,998
Uh, yes, Captain!

458
00:18:37,023 --> 00:18:37,813
What?

459
00:18:38,164 --> 00:18:39,124
As of right now,

460
00:18:39,149 --> 00:18:42,029
you'll feel the difference
there is between us!

461
00:18:42,824 --> 00:18:44,124
Mamoru Izawa is the one

462
00:18:44,149 --> 00:18:45,529
who will take
the free kick.

463
00:18:45,744 --> 00:18:47,034
They think we're weak!

464
00:18:47,059 --> 00:18:48,729
We'll show them we're not!

465
00:18:50,728 --> 00:18:52,219
Kojiro Hyuga
stops the ball

466
00:18:52,244 --> 00:18:53,494
with his body!

467
00:18:53,519 --> 00:18:55,849
Ah, but Tsubasa
runs directly at him

468
00:18:55,874 --> 00:18:57,074
to take the ball away!

469
00:18:57,456 --> 00:18:58,666
You're so annoying!

470
00:18:58,954 --> 00:19:01,534
You would think the final
score would stay tied

471
00:19:01,559 --> 00:19:03,059
given our abilities!

472
00:19:04,233 --> 00:19:05,447
But that's a mistake.

473
00:19:05,531 --> 00:19:07,241
Now, I'll show everyone
my power!

474
00:19:07,994 --> 00:19:09,324
-Go!
-Whoa!

475
00:19:09,454 --> 00:19:10,744
What a surprise!

476
00:19:10,769 --> 00:19:12,679
Hyuga decides to pass
the ball.

477
00:19:12,704 --> 00:19:14,164
Takeshi! Go!

478
00:19:14,284 --> 00:19:16,374
-Take a shot on goal!
-What?

479
00:19:16,494 --> 00:19:17,624
Yes, Captain!

480
00:19:18,314 --> 00:19:21,953
Takeshi Sawada launches
a long-distance shot!

481
00:19:22,454 --> 00:19:23,414
How stupid!

482
00:19:23,439 --> 00:19:25,874
Even my grandmother
could stop that shot!

483
00:19:27,079 --> 00:19:27,829
-Wait, what?!
-Huh?

484
00:19:27,874 --> 00:19:29,034
Incredible!

485
00:19:29,059 --> 00:19:30,454
The ball goes into
the net,

486
00:19:30,574 --> 00:19:32,914
and goalkeeper Morisaki
barely even moved!

487
00:19:33,034 --> 00:19:34,824
I'm...afraid...

488
00:19:34,914 --> 00:19:36,574
-of the ball!
-Huh?!

489
00:19:36,704 --> 00:19:38,314
Oh, so that was it!

490
00:19:38,339 --> 00:19:39,969
Hyuga shot directly
at the goalie

491
00:19:39,994 --> 00:19:42,034
to make him scared
of the ball!

492
00:19:42,244 --> 00:19:43,414
Darn it, Hyuga,

493
00:19:43,463 --> 00:19:45,053
how could you do that
to Yuzo?

494
00:19:45,664 --> 00:19:46,574
Yuzo Morisaki

495
00:19:46,599 --> 00:19:48,059
has no desire to
continue the match.

496
00:19:48,284 --> 00:19:50,534
Unfortunately,
Nankatsu only has one goalie

497
00:19:50,559 --> 00:19:52,149
and cannot make
a substitution.

498
00:19:52,744 --> 00:19:54,824
Captain Hyuga is
very intimidating.

499
00:19:54,954 --> 00:19:56,929
Yes, he is. Good thing
he plays for our team.

500
00:19:56,954 --> 00:19:58,454
Could you imagine
if he didn't?

501
00:19:58,994 --> 00:20:01,744
It's now two to one
in favor of Meiwa.

502
00:20:01,824 --> 00:20:04,250
Now Nankatsu is behind
on the scoreboard.

503
00:20:05,874 --> 00:20:07,374
Meiwa
attacks aggressively

504
00:20:07,399 --> 00:20:08,649
and has control
of the ball!

505
00:20:08,874 --> 00:20:09,914
Listen up!

506
00:20:10,034 --> 00:20:11,624
Now anyone can score!

507
00:20:11,744 --> 00:20:14,009
The goalie is just
an ornament now!

508
00:20:14,034 --> 00:20:15,784
-Idiots!
-Yeah!

509
00:20:17,204 --> 00:20:18,744
It looks like
Nankatsu's goalkeeper

510
00:20:18,744 --> 00:20:19,744
is petrified!

511
00:20:19,744 --> 00:20:21,164
His teammates
will have to block

512
00:20:21,189 --> 00:20:23,454
-the opposition's shots!
-Here it goes!

513
00:20:23,656 --> 00:20:25,744
-Yuzo, do something!
-Stop the ball!

514
00:20:25,744 --> 00:20:27,244
This looks like
the third goal!

515
00:20:27,374 --> 00:20:28,204
Ah!

516
00:20:28,229 --> 00:20:29,439
The ball is stopped!

517
00:20:29,464 --> 00:20:30,824
The center forward
of Nankatsu

518
00:20:30,824 --> 00:20:32,284
intercepts the ball
skillfully!

519
00:20:32,309 --> 00:20:33,875
That was a great play,
Tsubasa!

520
00:20:33,954 --> 00:20:34,954
See that, Meiwa?

521
00:20:35,169 --> 00:20:36,259
Our beloved Captain

522
00:20:36,284 --> 00:20:38,454
also knows
how to play defense too!

523
00:20:39,454 --> 00:20:40,934
-You see, Yuzo?
-Huh?

524
00:20:41,374 --> 00:20:43,954
The ball is our friend,
so don't fear it!

525
00:20:43,979 --> 00:20:44,979
What?

526
00:20:45,244 --> 00:20:47,204
That nosy idiot!

527
00:20:47,804 --> 00:20:48,804
No way!

528
00:20:49,024 --> 00:20:51,204
You think the ball's
your friend, huh?

529
00:20:51,534 --> 00:20:53,034
Well, if that's the case...

530
00:20:53,244 --> 00:20:54,954
Here it is.
Kiss it!

531
00:20:56,124 --> 00:20:56,824
Be careful, Tsubasa!

532
00:20:56,824 --> 00:20:57,994
Be careful!

533
00:20:58,124 --> 00:21:00,744
The ball
hits Tsubasa in the face!

534
00:21:00,874 --> 00:21:02,704
If you love the ball
so much,

535
00:21:02,729 --> 00:21:05,069
then how about you both
go into the goal!

536
00:21:05,284 --> 00:21:06,374
What?!

537
00:21:06,824 --> 00:21:08,219
Incredible!

538
00:21:08,244 --> 00:21:09,374
Tsubasa stops the ball

539
00:21:09,399 --> 00:21:11,689
with his hand and leg
against the posts!

540
00:21:12,744 --> 00:21:14,244
No! Tsubasa!

541
00:21:16,784 --> 00:21:18,784
See?
There's no need to fear it!

542
00:21:19,824 --> 00:21:20,824
Tsubasa...

543
00:21:23,124 --> 00:21:24,124
Oh...

544
00:21:24,784 --> 00:21:25,824
Thank you so much!

545
00:21:26,624 --> 00:21:28,124
Thank you, Tsubasa.

546
00:21:29,244 --> 00:21:30,534
I will defend the goal!

547
00:21:30,914 --> 00:21:32,744
-Now, I won't be afraid!
-That's it!

548
00:21:33,824 --> 00:21:35,824
Good!
That's the spirit, Yuzo!

549
00:21:36,664 --> 00:21:38,299
Nankatsu
has stopped another shot

550
00:21:38,324 --> 00:21:40,534
thanks to the brave play
of their captain,

551
00:21:40,664 --> 00:21:42,494
but Meiwa won't
stop attacking.

552
00:21:42,994 --> 00:21:44,784
This time you won't save it!

553
00:21:44,914 --> 00:21:45,784
Stop it, Yuzo!

554
00:21:45,784 --> 00:21:46,784
I got it!

555
00:21:47,624 --> 00:21:49,704
-Good job, Yuzo, you did it!
-Good job, Yuzo, you did it!

556
00:21:49,994 --> 00:21:50,994
Yes!

557
00:21:51,744 --> 00:21:53,494
The ball is my best friend!

558
00:21:53,954 --> 00:21:55,454
I won't ever let it go!

559
00:21:55,954 --> 00:21:57,244
Right, Tsubasa?

560
00:21:57,664 --> 00:21:58,664
Right!

561
00:21:58,874 --> 00:22:00,624
That twerp did it again!

562
00:22:00,824 --> 00:22:03,874
He got his goalie to
regain his confidence!

563
00:22:03,994 --> 00:22:05,874
Hyuga kicked the ball
directly at the goalie

564
00:22:05,994 --> 00:22:07,074
to make him scared.

565
00:22:07,182 --> 00:22:09,022
And then,
Tsubasa stopped the shot

566
00:22:09,047 --> 00:22:10,377
with his face
on purpose.

567
00:22:10,954 --> 00:22:11,994
But, why'd he do it?

568
00:22:12,494 --> 00:22:13,534
It's obvious.

569
00:22:13,744 --> 00:22:15,574
His intention was
to make the goalkeeper

570
00:22:15,704 --> 00:22:17,244
to regain the courage
he lost.

571
00:22:17,624 --> 00:22:18,624
Brilliant.

572
00:22:18,914 --> 00:22:19,914
Tsubasa...

573
00:22:19,939 --> 00:22:21,569
Really, thank you so much.

574
00:22:21,594 --> 00:22:23,914
You don't know how happy
I am you are our captain!

575
00:22:25,464 --> 00:22:27,014
Here you are, Tsubasa!

576
00:22:27,284 --> 00:22:28,744
Take good care of
our friend!

577
00:22:29,574 --> 00:22:32,414
Yes!
Now it's our turn to attack!

578
00:22:36,354 --> 00:22:41,354
[ending theme]
